an-gogh\/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"652\" height=\"489\" src=\"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/colour-2-3-edited.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-838 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/colour-2-3-edited.jpg 652w, https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/31\/2022\/03\/colour-2-3-edited-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\"><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/the-other-ways-to-look-at-van-gogh\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"115\">The Other Ways to Look At van Gogh<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Curator Karen Serres reflects on the role that portraiture plays in defining the post-Impressionist painter.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\" href=\"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/category\/culture\/\">Culture<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator alignwide\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">photo credits: Pexels<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>photo credits: Pexels<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-4","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/4","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/mccs-journalism.gold.ac.uk\/wp\/blurr\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"